<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="apparent-adj">apparent <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'pærənt/    美 /ə'pærənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-obvious">1.★ <strong>明显的；显而易见的(obvious)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It</strong> soon <strong>became apparent to everyone that</strong> he couldn’t sing.
很快大家都明白他不会唱歌。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>For no apparent reason</strong>, the train suddenly stopped.
不知什么原因，火车突然停了下来。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>表面上的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He did well in his exams, despite his apparent lack of interest in his work.
他考得很好，尽管表面上他对功课不感兴趣。</p></div></div>